tissueExpression.summary: Cytoplasmic expression at variable levels in several cell types.

Moderate cytoplasmic positivity, often with a granular pattern, was displayed in respiratory epithelia, gastro-intestinal glands, gall bladder, adrenal gland, fallopian tube, Leydig cells and heart myocytes. Hepatocytes, renal tubules and subset of placental trophoblastic cells were strongly stained. Remaining normal tissues were weakly stained or negative.

Weak to moderate cytoplasmic immunoreactivity, often with a granular pattern was observed in most cancer tissues. Malignant lymphomas, gliomas, cervical, skin, testicular and thyroid cancers were negative.
